Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over half of the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%packet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} and remaining Central American style spice mix.

Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person.

Pop the meatballs onto a baking tray and bake on the top shelf of your oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything bakes, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @burger sauce{45%g}. Set your coleslaw aside for later.

When everything's nearly ready, slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through) and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, transfer the buns to your #plates{} and spread the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} on the insides.

Fill your roll with the sausage meatballs and top with the caramelised onions.

Serve with your coleslaw and spiced fries alongside. Enjoy!